{"descriptions":[{"id":1381,"title":null,"content":"\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003eAbbreviations are very common in Literary Tibetan. They are of two kinds: phonic and graphic. The former usually occur only in the case of quadrisyllabic expressions, and consist of omitting the second and fourth syllables.\u003c/p\u003e \u003cul\u003e \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eབྱང་སེམས་\u003c/span\u003e = \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eབྱང་ཆུབ་སེམས་དཔའ་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;Bodhisattva\u0026rdquo; \u003c/li\u003e \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eདེ་གཤེགས་\u003c/span\u003e = \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eདེ་བཞིན་གཤེགས་པ་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;Tathāgata\u0026rdquo; \u003c/li\u003e \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཐེག་ཆེན་\u003c/span\u003e = \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཐེག་པ་ཆེན་པོ་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;Mahāyāna\u0026rdquo; \u003c/li\u003e \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཕྱག་རྡོར་\u003c/span\u003e = \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཕྱག་ན་རྡོ་རྗེ་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;The bodhisattva Vajrapāṇi (or Chakna Dorj\u0026eacute;)\u0026rdquo;\u003c/li\u003e \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eདགེ་སློབ་\u003c/span\u003e = \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eདགེ་རྒན་དང་སློབ་མ་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;Master and disciple(s)\u0026rdquo; \u003c/li\u003e \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཞིང་འབྲོག་\u003c/span\u003e = \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཞིང་པ་དང་འབྲོག་པ་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;Farmers and nomads\u0026rdquo;\u003c/li\u003e \u003c/ul\u003e \u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003eThe same principle applies in the spoken language for abridging personal names of four syllables:\u003c/p\u003e \u003cul\u003e \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཚེ་རྡོར་\u003c/span\u003e Tsedor = \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཚེ་རིང་རྡོ་རྗེ་\u003c/span\u003e Tsering Dorj\u0026eacute;\u003c/li\u003e \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eབཀྲ་དཔལ་\u003c/span\u003e Trapel = \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eབཀྲ་ཤིས་དཔལ་ལྡན་\u003c/span\u003e Trashi Penden\u003c/li\u003e \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཆོས་རྒྱམ་\u003c/span\u003e Ch\u0026ouml;gyam = \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཆོས་ཀྱི་རྒྱ་མཚོ་\u003c/span\u003e Ch\u0026ouml;kyi Gyatso (or Gyamtso)\u003c/li\u003e \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eབསོད་སྒྲོན་\u003c/span\u003e S\u0026ouml;dr\u0026ouml;n = \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eབསོད་ནམས་སྒྲོལ་མ་\u003c/span\u003e S\u0026ouml;nam Dr\u0026ouml;lma\u003c/li\u003e \u003c/ul\u003e \u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003eNote that in some cases, a resyllabification occurs whereby the prefixed or the superscribed letter of the following syllable is interpreted as the final of the preceding syllable. The written orthography records this phenomenon. For example, the last letter in Ch\u0026ouml;gyam or Tsedor belongs in fact to the fourth syllable (that has been omitted), respectively \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eམཚོ་\u003c/span\u003e and \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eརྗེ་\u003c/span\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e \u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003eGraphic abbreviations consist of using special signs to replace a group of letters. The following are the most common:\u003c/p\u003e \u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003eThe circle\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003e ༚\u003c/span\u003e, written above a letter, replaces the suffix \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eམ\u003c/span\u003e:\u003c/p\u003e \u003cul\u003e \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eལཾ་\u003c/span\u003e = \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eལམ་\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/li\u003e \u003c/ul\u003e \u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003eThe \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཊ་\u003c/span\u003e (reversed \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཏ་\u003c/span\u003e) substitutes for the suffix \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eགས་\u003c/span\u003e:\u003c/p\u003e \u003cul\u003e \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eལཊ་\u003c/span\u003e = \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eལགས་\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/li\u003e \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eལེཊ་\u003c/span\u003e = \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eལེགས་ \u003c/span\u003e\u003c/li\u003e \u003c/ul\u003e \u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003eThere are also abbreviations in which two syllables are graphically compacted into a single syllable:\u003c/p\u003e \u003cul\u003e \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eབོུ་\u003c/span\u003e = \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eབུ་མོ་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;Girl\u0026rdquo;\u003c/li\u003e \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཚོུ་\u003c/span\u003e = \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཆུ་ཚོད་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;Hour\u0026rdquo;\u003c/li\u003e \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eབཀྲིས་བདེ་ལེཊ་\u003c/span\u003e = \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eབཀྲ་ཤིས་བདེ་ལེགས་\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/li\u003e \u003c/ul\u003e","source_url":null,"is_primary":true,"created_at":"2013-09-15 04:15:46 UTC","updated_at":"2013-09-15 04:15:46 UTC","authors":[{"id":"6","fullname":"Nicolas Tournadre"}]}]}